    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>1.1 Data Accessed via Meta Graph API</h3>
    <p>When you log in using Facebook, we access the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your name (from your Facebook profile)</li>
      <li>Reactions (e.g., likes, loves) on your posts</li>
      <li>Comments on your posts</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This data is only accessed to provide functionality and is not stored in our database.</p>

    <h3>1.2 Session Data</h3>
    <p>We store the following in your encrypted session:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your Facebook user ID</li>
      <li>An access token for authentication</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Session data is deleted after 30 minutes of inactivity or upon logout.</p>

    <hr />

